<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id79fcacdb-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s5204"><num value="5204">§ 5204.</num><heading> Relationship to State and local law and civil actions</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">This chapter does not preempt a State law or local ordinance that provides for civil or criminal penalties for conduct that violates this chapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id79fcacdc-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/103/322/tXXXII/s320805">Pub. L. 103–322, title XXXII, § 320805</ref>, <date date="1994-09-13">Sept. 13, 1994</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/108/2122">108 Stat. 2122</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
